cjnIpAListMgmt.name: cjnIpAListMgmt
cjnIpAListMgmt.contactinfo: Tim Lai -- twlai@lucent.com Raj Duggal (Group Leader) -- rduggal@lucent.com Ira Steckler -- isteckler@lucent.com
cjnIpAListMgmt.description: The IP Access List Table for the Cajun Router.

ipACListCtlTable.name: ipACListCtlTable
ipACListCtlTable.description: This table is used to add/delete access list. This table maintain a list of access lists in the system. Each access list is made up of a group of access rule. The access rules are stored in the ipACRuleTable.

ipACListCtlEntry.name: ipACListCtlEntry
ipACListCtlEntry.description: The information concerning one of the IP access list.

ipACListCtlName.name: ipACListCtlName
ipACListCtlName.description: Entry Name. Access List Name. If this instance is a string that represent a number, the following rules applies: 1 to 99 - ipACListCtlType must set to standard 101 to 199 - ipACListCtlType must set to extended others - cannot be created If this instance is a string that does not represent a number, the ipACListCtlType must be set before ipACListCtlStatus becomes active.

ipACListCtlType.name: ipACListCtlType
ipACListCtlType.description: Type of Access List: unset (0) standard (1) extended (2) This instance cannot be changed once ipACListCtlStatus becomes active. The value of this instance must compile with the rule listed in the ipACListCtlName instance.

ipACListCtlStatus.name: ipACListCtlStatus
ipACListCtlStatus.description: For creation/deletion of IP access control statement. active (1) -- is set when both ipACListCtlName and ipACListCtlType is set. notInService (2) -- is set when ipACListCtlName or ipACListCtlType is not set. notReady (3) createAndGo (4) -- is set on creating new access list. createAndWait (5) destroy (6) -- is set on destroying an existed access list. The management should inspect the ipACRuleTable and delete all the related entries. An entry in the ipACRuleTable is related to this entry if ipACListCtlName equals ipACRuleName.

ipACRuleTable.name: ipACRuleTable
ipACRuleTable.description: This table is used to add/delete individual access rule statement in an access list.

ipACRuleEntry.name: ipACRuleEntry
ipACRuleEntry.description: The ipAccessRuleEntry control all the conditional fields and its parameters for an access rule.

ipACRuleName.name: ipACRuleName
ipACRuleName.description: Entry Name. Access List Name. This object identifies which access list this access rule belongs to. This object shall identify the instance of the ipACListCtlEntry object.

ipACRuleSubIndex.name: ipACRuleSubIndex
ipACRuleSubIndex.description: Entry sub index. Each access list entry may has multiple rules. This sub index identified each rule.

ipACRuleOwner.name: ipACRuleOwner
ipACRuleOwner.description: The string identifies the media which was used to create/modify this access rule. Local indicates creation via web, cli or snmp. external indicates an external client (ie. CajunRules)

ipACRuleSrcAddr.name: ipACRuleSrcAddr
ipACRuleSrcAddr.description: The IP address of the source address. A value of 0 in ipACListSrcMask indicates this is a DON'T CARE field.

ipACRuleSrcAddrWild.name: ipACRuleSrcAddrWild
ipACRuleSrcAddrWild.description: This field specifies the wildcard of the source IP address.

ipACRuleSrcMask.name: ipACRuleSrcMask
ipACRuleSrcMask.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. The MASK address of the source address. A value of 0 indicates this field and ipACListSrcAddr are DON'T CARE

ipACRuleSrcMaskWild.name: ipACRuleSrcMaskWild
ipACRuleSrcMaskWild.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. This field specifies the wildcard of the source IP mask.

ipACRuleDstAddr.name: ipACRuleDstAddr
ipACRuleDstAddr.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. The IP address of the destination address. A value of 0 in ipAccessListDstMask indicates this is a DON'T CARE field.

ipACRuleDstAddrWild.name: ipACRuleDstAddrWild
ipACRuleDstAddrWild.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. This field specifies the wildcard of the destination IP address.

ipACRuleDstMask.name: ipACRuleDstMask
ipACRuleDstMask.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. The MASK address of the destination address. A value of 0 indicates this field and ipACListDstAddr are DON'T CARE

ipACRuleDstMaskWild.name: ipACRuleDstMaskWild
ipACRuleDstMaskWild.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. This field specifies the wildcard of the destination IP mask.

ipACRuleOperation.name: ipACRuleOperation
ipACRuleOperation.description: How to operate the IP ACCESS CONTROL statement, on the receiving packet.

ipACRuleProtocol.name: ipACRuleProtocol
ipACRuleProtocol.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. Over which protocol does the IP ACCESS CONTROL statement activate. A value of 65536 is don't care. A value of 65537 means both TCP and UDP. Note: Cajun P550 does not allow ipACListProtocol equal to TCP or UDP because of hardware limitation. This limitation will be lift in the future.

ipACRuleL4SrcPortMin.name: ipACRuleL4SrcPortMin
ipACRuleL4SrcPortMin.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. If ipACRuleProtocol is TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), this field and ipACListL4SrcPortMax specifies a range of source ports. This field specifies the lower bound of the port range for the access rule. A value of 65536 is don't care. This field has no meaning if ipACRuleProtocol is not TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), and it should be 65536.

ipACRuleL4SrcPortMax.name: ipACRuleL4SrcPortMax
ipACRuleL4SrcPortMax.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. If ipACRuleProtocol is TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), this field and ipACListL4SrcPortMin specifies a range of source ports. This field specifies the upper bound of the port range for the access rule. A value of 65536 is don't care. This field has no meaning if ipACRuleProtocol is not TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), and it should be 65536.

ipACRuleL4DestPortMin.name: ipACRuleL4DestPortMin
ipACRuleL4DestPortMin.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. If ipACRuleProtocol is TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), this field and ipACListL4DestPortMax specifies a range of destination ports. This field specifies the lower bound of the port range for the access rule. A value of 65536 is don't care. This field has no meaning if ipACRuleProtocol is not TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), and it should be 65536.

ipACRuleL4DestPortMax.name: ipACRuleL4DestPortMax
ipACRuleL4DestPortMax.description: The instance is not writable if the corresponding ipACListCtlType is standard. If ipACRuleProtocol is TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), this field and ipACListL4DestPortMin specifies a range of destination ports. This field specifies the upper bound of the port range for the access rule. A value of 65536 is don't care. This field has no meaning if ipACRuleProtocol is not TCP(6), UDP(17), or TCP & UDP(65536), and it should be 65536.

ipACRuleStatus.name: ipACRuleStatus
ipACRuleStatus.description: For create/delete of a IP access rule statement. active (1) notInService (2) notReady (3) createAndGo (4) createAndWait (5) destroy (6) createAndWait and createAndGo is set on creating new access list. destory is set on destroying access rule. active is set when all the required instance is set in the entry.

ipACRuleEstablished.name: ipACRuleEstablished
ipACRuleEstablished.description: This field indicates an established TCP connection.

ipACRuleLog.name: ipACRuleLog
ipACRuleLog.description: This field indicates whether the access-list should log information.

ipForwardCtlEnabled.name: ipForwardCtlEnabled
ipForwardCtlEnabled.description: The object control the enable or disable the forwarding control mechanism in the system.

ipForwardCtlACName.name: ipForwardCtlACName
ipForwardCtlACName.description: This object identifies which access list to use for IP forward control. This object shall identify the instance of the ipACListCtlEntry object.
